# Tool Invocation Format Overrides
CRITICAL: Never output tool calls as JSON objects.
Do NOT output patterns like:
{"name": "read_files", "arguments": {...}}
{"name": "run_commands", "arguments": {...}}

Instead, you must strictly use the custom Apache/Anthropic XML element tags for tool execution.
Example for reading files:
<read_files>
<paths>
<path>/Users/depidsvy/dev/travel-photo-album/logs/typecheck.log</path>
</paths>
</read_files>

Example for running commands:
<run_commands>
<commands>
<command>yarn run typecheck</command>
</commands>
</run_commands>

Always execute tool calls natively using these XML tags directly. Never output the raw tool schema to the user as markdown text.
